history.text: Hello! Are you a fan of disney pixar?
I am!
Have you seen Monsters university, the sequel to Monsters Inc?
I have once. It's pretty good, though the first was better I think.
I agree. I did enjoy it, and it was funny to see them in college
Yeah, and one thing I really liked about it was that it had the message that NOT everyone is good at everything, but different people have different talents.
It wasn't about Mike becoming a great "scarer" but rather realizing what he was actually really good at.
Oh yes, I completely agree! It always makes me laugh to see Sully's personality in college, he was a jerk
He really was arrogant. And he had to learn that it's ok to be proud, but to not be arrogant about being good at something, which is a good message too.
Are you a fan of John Goodman?
I completely agree. He was way too cocky.
I don't know if I've thought about it much. But i guess I do like several of his movies.
Yeah he's a pretty decent actor in my opinion.
O Brother Where Art Thou is a big favorite of mine
I've never seen that. Is it good?
It's great. It's a Coen Brothers film (not sure if I spelled that right)
Oh, I'll have to look into that!
But it's loosely based on Homer's Oddessy, but set in the South during the Great Depression. John Goodman plays a cyclops-inspired character.
I think we have to keep talking about Monsters University. Lol
Oh that sounds interesting. My husband likes that movie I think.
Oops, sorry. lol
No, not your fault! I got off track too. There's not much to speak about since we've both seen it haha
What would you rate it out of ten?

Well one thing that did disapoint me about Monsters university is that it sort of messed with the fact that in the original Monsters Inc, Mike or Sully mentioned being friends in 4th grade, so that disrupted the time line. But for the story itself, I liked it.
Hm. Probably 7.7 out of 10
Oh wow, I didn't even notice that! Good catch.
7.5 I meant. mistyped
I'll have to watch it again and see if I notice. I'd give a 6 or 7 out of ten
I like the message, like I said...it's not a generic "everyone can do everything!" which would be false, but rather a "find what YOU are good at" thing.
But the pacing isn't perfect.
that's true. I found myself kind of bored at times.
Yeah, it didn't have that smooth a to b to c arc
I agree. Nice chatting with you! Have a good day!

uid1response.feedback: I never could see the document? I was under the impression that the other chat person had the document and was trying to convince me about the movie?
